# Eval case: ai-financial-doc-qa

IDEA="Create a local Gen-AI question-answering assistant over a user's personal financial documents (bank statements, salary slips, policy PDFs). Build an on-device RAG index, retrieve relevant passages, and have a local LLM answer natural-language questions grounded strictly in retrieved chunks with citations. Everything runs offline; documents never leave the machine."

CONTEXT="Target: single user, laptop-only, fully offline. Stack: Python CLI; local embeddings (sentence-transformers); FAISS vector store; SQLite (encrypted) for metadata; Ollama 8B for answering. Formats: PDF; TXT; CSV documents. Limits: max 500 documents; answers must cite source chunks. Non-goals: cloud embeddings; cloud LLM default; React UI; multi-user; uploading documents anywhere; financial advice/recommendations; tax filing. Defer: spreadsheet formula reasoning; multi-language OCR; chat memory across sessions."
